-- Alexander Anderson Dictionaries Notes

-- What is a dictionary?
-- A list that contains a key and a value pair.

-- example:
--     car = {
--         "make":"Ford",
--         "model":"EscapeXLT",
--         "year": 2008,
--         "color": "Red",
--     }

--     print(car) would print {"make","Ford","model","EscapeXLT","year", 2008, "color", "Red"}



-- What are keys?
-- A group of names that have information/values inside them



-- What are values?
-- The values inside the keys that can be accesed via the keys



-- How do you write a dictionary?
-- name_of_dictionary = {
--     "key": "Data"
--     "key": "Data"
--     "key": "Data"
--     etc...
-- }



-- What data types can you have in a dictionary?
-- any



-- How do you print 1 item from a dictionary?
-- print[item_placement[can go to item inside item with brackets]]



-- Why would you use a dictionary in a program?
-- avatar = {
